A METRO MAP METAPHOR FOR ORGANIZING WEB-BASED RESOURCES -- tKNOWLEDGE MANAGEMENT AT THE FINNISH GOVERNMENT -- tA KNOWLEDGE PARTNERSHIP IN PORTUGUESE INFORMATION AND KNOWLEDGE SERVICES -- tCORPORATE BUNKER OR CYBER CAFÉ: RETHINKING THE STRATEGIC ROLE OF THE LIBRARY IN THE CORPORATION - A CASE STUDY0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aAnerkanntermaßen stellt das Konzept des Knowledge Management einen entscheidenden Gewinn für den Informationsprofi dar. Management-Theorien betonen immer die wichtige Rolle von Bibliotheken und Bibliothekare in der Praxis von Organisationen (Unternehmen, Städte aber auch die gesamte Gesellschaft). Die in diesem Band enthaltenen Beiträge demonstrieren dies aus der Sicht der Bibliotheken. In diesen Beiträgen werden grundlegende Implikationen des Knowledge Management als zentralem Arbeitsfeld in Bibliotheken diskutiert, Grundsatzfragen und Methoden analysiert und praktische Beispiele untersucht. Unter den Autoren finden sich beispielsweise Larry Prusak, James Matarazzo, Michael Koenig, Rafael Capurro, Susan Henczel, Irene Wormell und Rainer Kuhlen. Das Buch vereint 18 wichtige Texte zum Thema: z. B. aus IFLA-Workshops und -Konferenzen, aber auch aus anderen Quellen, wie beispielsweise der SLA (Special Libraries Association).  aIt is a widely accepted that Knowledge Management constitutes a key asset for the information professional. Management theory has always pointed to the fact that libraries and librarians in particular play an important role in an organization (be it an enterprise, a city, or a society as a whole). The papers collected in this volume demonstrate why and how - from the libraries' perspective. They discuss some fundamental implications of Knowledge Management as a key activity area for libraries, analyse key issues and instruments and give some best practice examples. Among the contributing authors the reader will find Larry Prusak, James Matarazzo, Michael Koenig, Rafael Capurro, Susan Henczel, Irene Wormell and Rainer Kuhlen. The book brings together eighteen important texts for the topic not only from IFLA workshops and conferences but also from other sources such as the SLA (Special Libraries Association). The inclusion of several original contributions makes this reader essential for all concerned with the future role of the library in business and society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aGestion des connaissances. 0aInformation organization. 0aInformation services. 0aKnowledge management. 0aOrganizational learning. 4aAufsatzsammlung. 4aBibliothek. 4aWissensmanagement. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Library & Information Science / General.2bisacsh1 aACCART, Jean-Philippe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBang, Tove, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCapurro, Rafael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChaudhry, Abdus Sattar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavenport, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavenport, Thomas H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHenczel, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHiggins, Susan E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHobohm, Hans-Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHobohm, Hans-Christoph, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJacobson, Alvin L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJussilainen, Maija, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoenig, Michael E.D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.